profile.summary:
Just raised a PR (Pull Request).

Do you know what I did in that PR? Well just solved a problem. That's it. That's what I do, solve problems using the power of data and algorithms.

Professionally speaking, as a Machine Learning Engineer, my job is to solve problems for my organization using data and algorithms. I design and develop Machine Learning based applications/services using various cutting-edge technologies.

Personally speaking, as a passionate coder, sometimes I spent more time working on personal projects than my professional work projects. These personal projects include random experiments with new frameworks/libraries, building open-source libraries, or maybe building a full-fledged product. Check my GitHub for more of my projects.

Other than coding, in my personal time, I like to travel to different places. read a lot of books, and listen to music. watch movies, etc

Now here are some of my skills
1. Algorithms, Data Structure, and Problem Solving. Machine Learning and Deep Learning, Predictive Modelling, Classification, Regression, and Backend Development.
2. Languages: Python, JavaScript, C++, HTML, CSS
3. Frameworks/Libraries: Tensorflow, Keras, PyTorch, SkLearn, Numpy, Pandas, Matplotlib, Flask, FastAPI, ExpressJS
4. Database: SQL (MSSQL, MySQL, PostgreSQL), NoSQL(MongoDB)
5. Cloud Platforms: Azure (Azure ML, App Service, Azure Blob, etc), AWS (EC2, S3, SageMaker, etc) 

Use these links to connect with me:
 1. Personal Website: https://imdeepmind.com/
 2. Github Account: https://github.com/imdeepmind/
 3. Blogs on Medium: https://medium.com/@imdeepmind/
 
Some of my personal projects:
 1. Delphy: https://delphyy.com/
 2. Hocrox: https://hocrox.imdeepmind.com/

projects.description:
ResearchNote is an ultra minimalistic open-source simple note-taking app developed using Python, Flask, React, and Ant Design.

The following are the highlights of Research Notes:
- Ultra minimalistic and super clean UI
- Provides a rich editor with supports like advanced formating, emojis, etc
- Supports a handy search method to search notes
- Open-Source
- 100% Free and always will be
